body:
This changes switches over the embedded browser to using the DevTools server that starts on project open rather than starting an instance of DevTools server associated with an app.

For bazel projects this currently opens a local daemon instance, but this will be changed once the run script is updated.

comment_data.body: expose the Future directly instead of providing a method that might lock the UI thread.

simpler pattern:
rather than starting a pooled thread just call
`AsyncUtils.whenCompleteUiThread(DevToolsService.getInstance(myProject).getDevToolsInstance(), ...)`
and remove the invokeLater.
I originally wanted this function to manage restarting if the daemon command fails, but that can be done elsewhere too
nit: this is java. Keep private and provide getDevToolsInstance()
make sure the project has not gone away while you were waiting for the devToolsServer to start.

commit.message: Modify for tests and remove unused methods
Expose instance future and use async utils
Remove println and complete with exception when null
Use instance getter and skip if project has closed
